	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ahh- Level 12 spells are nice. The best one to get is Shock of Lightning. For a mere 60 Manna you can deal out approximately 80 points of damage, in short order. Many other spells at this level are useful, especially in combination with lower level spells. Such as Bind Affinity. While it's true you can only bind others in a city (or other approved) zone, you may bind yourself anywhere. This can be used with the Gate spell for a wonderful travel combo.<BR>
<BR>
Halo of light, while producing an annoying light, which Dark Elves do not need, should not be overlooked, because it is also a +3 AC lore item.<BR>
<BR>
Frost Spiral however is a rather dissapointing area spell that only does around 40 damage for 100 manna. Column of frost is a much better choice, even though it is a lower level, as it does up to 31 damage for 39 manna. That means you can cast it twice, and still have manna leftover.<BR>
<BR>
Of course- your still going to need to save a space for that old tried and true root spell. So you can fry them without getting slapped and interupted. The good news is that by level 14 and 15 your channeling is getting good enough that you might actually REGAIN your concentration every once in a blue moon, and finish that darned spell.
				</font>
			</td>

