	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				At level 16 wizards actually become dangerous!<BR>
<BR>
The new sheild spell allows you some real defense, especially when combined with sheildskin, and the new offensive spells are great.<BR>
<BR>
Flameshock is probably the most efficient- at around 104 damage for 75 manna. But don't rule out Lightning bolt which does a whopping 117 for 85 manna. Even though this spell has the same limitations as Bolt of Fire (line of sight only, and it misses on occasion) it is worth the risk when you want to take something down FAST. These two spells would be reason enough to rejoice- but there is at least one other effective offense spell- Pillar of Fire. Finally an Area Effect spell that does decent damage (68) for a not unreasonable amount of manna (89).<BR>
If Project Lightning is as good I'll be even happier, but those accursed Runes are a Royal Pain to hunt down, and then you are likely to flub the first several attempts to create the scroll.<BR>
Also one other spell that is of vital importance. Wizards have to wait until level 16 to get invisibility. But when you do get it it may prove frustrating if you haven't kept up your Divination skills. (I know, Invisibility should be an Alteration- How could a spell designed to hide information be a divination? But I'm not the coder)<BR>
Once Invisibility is mastered- use it. A lot. It is extremely useful for attacking from ambush. For once you don't have to worry about making sure you get the root on for a good first strike, or making sure the tank has it's attention. Sure they are going to come after you anyway once you slap one for 117 damage, but at least you get to pick when and where.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
