	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Level 1-3<BR>
I started as a human wizard in Qeynos. Therefore, I am telling this from the point of view of Qeynos-bound human wizard. It took me about an hour to learn the city well, and then I was off to my guild. (By the way, in my experience, the maps in the EverQuest manual are all but useless and just get you lost. Shout for the location or blunder aroud until you find what you are looking for yourself.) Get your spells memorized and put 2 training into Channeling, 2 into Evocation and one into piercing. Go out and fry some baddies. Attack bats, snakes, decaying skeletons (ALWAYS attack decaying skeletons), and gnoll pups. (Kill them, too.) You should level quickly. By the end of level 2 you should have bought Numbing Cold. It has helped me many times when being teamed up on. It is now your choice of what weapon type you should pursue. Either pick piercing and get a Giant Snake Fang, or go with blunt (staffs). I chose piercing, but I switched to blunt later on because of magic staffs. At level 3, migrate into the hills and kill the low level stuff there. Also get a trade skill now or the next level. They will get you much money later on. I suggest jewelcraft or fishing. Fishing is easy and you will nedd a lot of the items you can make with jewelry.<BR>
Level 4-7<BR>
NEW SPELLS! Get Shock of Fire, Gate, Root, Icestrike, and O'Keils Radiation. Your spell bar should be full. Use Shock of Fire as your main attack spell. A few words on the other spells:<BR>
Icestrike good for attacking large groups from a distance. If you ever see a large group already engaged at a distance, use Icestrike<BR>
O'Keils: Only use on other PCs while they are fighting. This spell makes you friends quickly.<BR>
Gate: DO NOT, I repeat DO NOT use this spel when being attacked. It will either fizzle or get interrupted. Get someewhere safe if you are being chased before gating. It also helps to get back to Qeynos when a distance off.<BR>
Root: PRACTICE THIS INTO THE GROUND. I did not find out until later how USEFUL this spell is. Eventually, they will be stuck long ant stuck strong if you use it enough.<BR>
Ok, then. Now go out and kill. You are buffed and ready. AT about this level, you will want armor. GEt a Senior Apprentice Robe (good for this level) and cloth armor. Get jewelry as you have the money, but when you have it get 2 onyx earings and 2 jaded silver rings. At level 5, head into BlackBorough. It is a great place to level. Hunt there until you are old and grey. At level 7, you might want to start to explore the Karana Plains. DONT BITE OFF MORE THAN YOU CAN CHEW.<BR>
Level 8-12<BR>
I am only level 9, so this is all I can say. Get Shock of Ice, Lesser Shielding, Fingers of Fire, Fire Bolt, and Shadow Step. Replace Minor Shielding with Lesser Shielding, Shock of Frost with Shock of Ice, Numbing Cold with Fingers of Fire, and O'Keil's Radiation with Fire Bolt. Do hte same thing you have been doing. The stradegy is Root, then blast. Dont memorize Shadow Step, maybe not even buy it, but I like collecting spells, and Shadow Step is fun and in some cases useful. Dont use Fire Bolt overmuch until level 9, because it eats mana like a ***** and you will need it. A LOT. Good luck with your Wizard and show those Sabertooths who is boss!<BR>
-Thynfiula
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
